      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, using generator functions is a smart move when dealing with large datasets and memory constraints. A list comprehension builds the entire list in memory at once, which is what's causing your `MemoryError`. A generator, on the other hand, yields one item at a time, keeping memory usage low. You can process the data chunk by chunk, which is much more efficient for big CSVs.",
