      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the example. that helps a lot. regarding those memory spikes u mentioned—is there a way to track down what specifically is \"eating\" the RAM? like if it's a leak or just a really inefficient part of the code that's hogging resources, how do i actually see what's responsible for the sudden drop in available memory?",
