    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Tracking down the exact memory hog in Python can be tricky, but you can definitely get a better idea of what's causing the spike. You can use the built-in `memory_profiler` library, which is fantastic for this. It lets you decorate functions and measure the memory usage line by line.\n\nYou can use the `@profile` decorator on the function that is causing the trouble, and then run your script with the `mprof` command. It will generate a report showing exactly how much memory each line of your code consumes. It's a very precise way to see where the resource drain is happening.",
